Subject: Re: [VB] stuipd RGB question

At 08:00 PM 4/22/03 -0500, you wrote:
>I looked in the owners manuals online & the Bentley but have not
>found exactly what I am looking for. Found plenty of post about the
>amount of fluid & type of fluid to put in the tranny & RGB's, but how
>do you check the amount in the RGB? Sure the tranny is easy, just fill
>till it is even w/ the bottom of the fill plug., but is there anyway
>to check the RGB, or is it just assumed that if the tranny fluid is
>the correct level, the needed oil for the RGB's make their way to the
>correct level through the axle tubes.

Fill 'em to the top, through the plug.  Clean the crap out before you take 
the plug out.  Fill the RGB ~before~ you fill the tranny.  That stuff flows 
s_l_o_w_l_y -- the tranny will seem full, but a half hour later it will all 
flow out to the RGB and the tranny will be empty...

Jeff
